Here are both approaches for .NET MAUI Shell navigation:

**1. Passing a simple string ID:**

```csharp
// ProductListPage.xaml.cs or ViewModel
async void OnProductSelected(Product product)
{
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"{nameof(ProductDetailsPage)}?productId={product.Id}");
}
```

**2. Passing the full object (via dictionary):**

```csharp
async void OnProductSelected(Product product)
{
    var parameters = new Dictionary<string, object>
    {
        { "product", product }
    };
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync(nameof(ProductDetailsPage), parameters);
}
```

**Receiving both on the ViewModel with `IQueryAttributable`:**

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach 1: simple string parameter
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var idObj))
        {
            string productId = idObj.ToString();
            // fetch product from service, etc.
            LoadProduct(productId);
        }

        // Approach 2: full object
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var productObj) && productObj is Product product)
        {
            Name = product.Name;
            Price = product.Price;
            // use directly — no extra fetch needed
        }
    }
}
```

**Wire it up — register the route and bind the VM:**

```csharp
// AppShell.xaml.cs
Routing.RegisterRoute(nameof(ProductDetailsPage), typeof(ProductDetailsPage));

// MauiProgram.cs
builder.Services.AddTransient<ProductDetailsPage>();
builder.Services.AddTransient<ProductDetailsViewModel>();
```

```xml
<!-- ProductDetailsPage.xaml -->
<ContentPage x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailsViewModel" ... >
```

```csharp
// ProductDetailsPage.xaml.cs
public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
{
    InitializeComponent();
    BindingContext = vm;
}
```

**Key differences:**

| | String param | Object param |
|---|---|---|
| **Passed via** | URL query string | `Dictionary<string, object>` |
| **Survives deep link** | ✅ Yes | ❌ No |
| **Avoids extra fetch** | ❌ Need to load | ✅ Already have it |
| **Type in `ApplyQueryAttributes`** | `string` | Original type (cast needed) |

Use **string IDs** for deep-linkable/bookmarkable navigation; use **object passing** when you already have the data and want to avoid a redundant lookup.
